The paper focuses on generating photorealistic images of 3D object models for training object detectors, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The approach involves rendering complete scenes with realistic materials and lighting (graphics, cs.GR), generating plausible geometric configurations using physics simulations (robotics, cs.RO), and using a convolutional neural network for object detection (machine learning, cs.LG; artificial intelligence, cs.AI).
